<br>
The spell effects have a duration of 4-6 seconds.<br>
Similar spell effects overwrite wizard effects.<br>
Fire spells do not stack with Fire spells, ect....<br>
The spells have a casting time of 3 secs, Refresh time of 2.5 secs, and a Recast time of 7 secs.<br>
The spells have 2 restance checks, one for the damage and one for the Effect.<br>
The Damage portion of the spell can have partial resists.<br>
<br>
level 39, effect Cancel Magic, 300 damage, 200 mana, type Magic.<br>
level 44, effect Root, 300 damage, 200 mana, type Ice.<br>
level 49, effect Lower Str (50), 300 damage, 200 mana, type Fire.<br>
level 51, effect Lower ATK (200), 400 damage, 250 mana, type Magic.<br>
level 52, effect Snare, 400 damage, 250 mana, type Ice.<br>
level 53, effect Lower Agi (50), 400 damage, 250 mana, type Fire.<br>
level 54, effect Malo, 500 damage, 300 mana, type Magic.<br>
level 55, effect Slow, 500 damage, 300 mana, type Ice.<br>
level 56, effect Lower AC (300), 500 damage, 300 mana, type Fire.<br>
level 57, effect Lower Mob Melee Damage (25%), 600 damage, 400 mana, type Magic.<br>
level 58, effect Mem blur, 600 damage, 400 mana, type Ice.<br>
level 59, effect Mana Theft* (100), 600 damage, 400 mana, type Fire.<br>
<br>
**** I would like to see the level 60 spells be rains AEs Where each &quot;wave&quot; has a different effect.***<br>
<br>
level 60, effect Lower ATK (300), effect 2 Malo, effect 3 Lower mob melee damage (30%), 700 damage, 450 mana, type Magic.<br>
level 60, effect Snare, effect 2 Slow, effect 3 Mem blur, 700 damage, 450 mana, type Ice.<br>
level 60, effect Lower Agi (75), effect 2 Lower AC (400), effect 3 Mana theft (150), 700 damage, 450 mana, type Magic.<br>
<br>
* Mana Theft steals mana from the target, but does not give it to the caster.<br>
<br>
